                    h3 verPE description
                    p.
                        verPE is used to get the version of an executable file (exe, scr, sys, dll, etc.) in PE
                        (Portable Executable) format. (PE, "Portable Executable") is an executable, object code,
                        and dynamic link library format used by 32-bit and 64-bit versions of the Microsoft Windows
                        operating system. To get the version of the file, used the verPE.exe program,
                        which is located in the directory with the collector.

                    h3 Parameters
                    ul.browser-default
                        li.
                            Comma separated files - a list of files separated by commas. The list must contain the
                            full path to the file. Spaces before and after each file name will be removed.
                            For example: "C:\Windows\regedit.exe, C:\windows\notepad.exe"
                        li.
                            Return in version|filename format - return the result in version|filename format,
                            for example "10.0.19041.860 (WinBuild.160101.0800)|C:\Windows\regedit.exe"
                        li.
                            Return first result (not an array) - return the first result, not an array.
                            Used when you want to get a version for only one file. In this case, only version
                            information will be saved in history, and not an array in string representation.
                            ("10.0.19041.860" and not '["10.0.19041.860"]')
                    h3 Returned value
                    p.
                        By default, the file version is returned ("10.0.19041.860"). If the file contains no version,
                        an empty string is returned. If Return in version|filename format is active, the file version
                        and filename are returned
                        ("10.0.19041.860 (WinBuild.160101.0800)|C:\Windows\notepad.exe" or "|C:\Windows\runMe.bat")
                    p.
                        If multiple files are specified in the "Comma separated files" parameter and
                        the "Return first result (not an array)" parameter is not active, the following occurs:
                    ul.browser-default
                        li The entire resulting array of values is converted to JSON text and saved to a database with a history of values
                        li.
                            If the counter has dependent counters, then ALEPIZ will call them as many times as the
                            values are received in the array and each time pass the %:PARENT_VALUE:% new value from
                            the value array as a variable.

